column2: AI is basically computer generated intelligence , it can help to solve problems and can adapt to any user. It is not the same as my definition of intelligence

I think that AI is more of a computer learning model that doesn't have emotional capability, whereas human intelligence, which still may be algorithmic, takes into account factors like emotions and opinions that computers can't.
AI is a system that uses human intelligence. It uses only human intelligence, so it has the same definition as intelligence.
computerized programs that perform tasks humans normally do

AI is also known as artificial intelligence, a form of intelligence and understanding of information displayed in non-human forms such as technology. It is very different from my definition of intelligence.

I think AI is computer learning system which utilizes learning and memory to adapt to the environment, as well as having the advantage of access to the entire web. It is similar to my definition of intelligence in that revolves around problem solving, however I believe humans have further aspects to consider such as emotions and morals, which cannot be quantified by AI.

I think of AI the field dedicated to build artificial person-like agents, so going by that, what I imagine a "strong" Ai to be is definitionally the same as my idea of (human) intelligence. In practice, we use AI to describe a whole laundry list of things that doesn't match up with what we conceive as intelligence.
